# Security Intelligence Sharing
**Date:** 2025-11-10  
**Course:** CySA+ Certify Breakfast  
**Source:** Video Part 6  

---

## üß† Key Concepts
- ISACs
- Risk Management and Security Engineering
- Incident Response
- Vulnerability Management
  - The Process
    - Assign responsibilities
    - Document EVERYTHING
    - Management and User support
    - Inventory ~ keep track of devices, assets, configurations; collect and back up
    - Assign business risks and prioritize (How badly would we suffer if this device was comprimized?)
    - Select the right tools (the right ones for the vulnerability)
    - Scan for vulnerabilities
    - Fix ASAP; do not forget about it
- Detection and Monitoring

## üß© Important Terms / Commands
| Term | Definition |
|------|-------------|
| ISACs | Information Sharing and Analysis Centers; collects and shares information related to security, common vulnerabilities and attacks |

## üß† Takeaways / Real-World Use
- Vulnerability Management is a very important process. You're able to fix gaps in security BEFORE any issues or attacks happen. What do we need to fix? Where are our weaknesses?
  - Can be time consuming, but will also save you lots of $ compared to an actual attack or breach occuring.
- Detection and Monitoring will help fine tune your defenses, avoid false negatives and positives. Ensure you keep everything up to date.

